Thrombotic and hemorrhagic complications in chronic myeloproliferative disorders. Bleeding and thrombosis are major causes of morbidity and mortality in patients with chronic myeloproliferative disorders. We retrospectively evaluated 101 consecutive patients affected by primary thrombocytosis (46 male, 55 female, aged 18-84 years mean +/- SD 61 +/- 15) followed for a period ranging from 6 months up to 10 years (median 5 years) at our hematological unit. At the time of diagnosis 48 patients were asymptomatic